This code is very compact and stand-alone (almost dependent system)
So it is not so fancy option.
If you need change something, you have to change the code.






What you need:
====================================
ROOT 5.34/35
gcc compiler(general)






Codes:
====================================
TDISMC_EIC.cpp  :  pion structure function with ep scattering at JLEIC
TDISMC_EICn.cpp :  pion structure function with eD scattering at JLEIC
TDISMC_EICK.cpp :  kaon structure function with ep scattering at JLEIC
cteq/           :  cteqpdf.h and data based call files (c++ wrapper)
cteq-tbls/      :  nucleon PDFs table
tim_hobbs/      :  various regularization form for pion FF 






How to run:
====================================
> root -q -b batch.cc
> ls -lt
total 1168
-rw-r--r--   1 parkkj  JLAB\clas  210892 Dec 15 12:06 TDIS-MC05x100.root  (This is ROOT output)


** mainx(0.01,0.3,1,100,10001)
                          |-------- for creating random number seed
	              |------------ Q2 max
		  |---------------- Q2 min
		|------------------ xBj max
	   |----------------------- xBj min


*** You can turn on the Lund text output for GEMC simulation

Uncomment out following line 
	  //  OUTPUT FOR GEMC 
	     remove the comment sign;
	     /*
	        .........
	                      */

*** For GEMC installation
(assume one has the GEMC or know how to install/run)




How to change;
====================================
1) number of gen.event
2) incoming beam energy: PBeam, kBeam
3) beam emittances:
4) define the regularization form

modify "TDISMC_EIC.h"

